(43, 15, 5, 47, 13, 8, 8, 'for without me ye can do nothing', 'Connection of Action and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of divine support for effective action. John 15:5 states that without Christ, one can do nothing, while 2 Corinthians 13:8 asserts that one can do nothing against the truth, highlighting the importance of aligning with truth for fruitful outcomes.', 'theme', 0.685, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 5, 43, 5, 19, 19, 'for without me ye can do nothing', 'Dependence on Divine Source', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of reliance on a higher power. John 15:5 highlights that without Christ, one can do nothing, while John 5:19 states that the Son can do nothing of himself, indicating a shared theme of dependence.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 40, 7, 19, 19, NULL, 'Judgment of Non-productive Entities', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of failing to produce good fruit, leading to destruction. They illustrate the idea that those who do not abide or bear fruit are ultimately cast into the fire.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 58, 6, 7, 8, 'cast forth as a branch', 'Judgment of Unfruitful Entities', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of those who do not produce good fruit. John 15:6 speaks of branches that are cast into the fire, while Hebrews 6:8 describes earth that bears thorns and is rejected, leading to burning.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 40, 13, 41, 41, 'cast forth as a branch', 'Judgment and Separation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering and removal of those who do not abide in righteousness. John 15:6 speaks of branches being cast into the fire, while Matthew 13:41 describes angels gathering out of the kingdom those who offend and do iniquity.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 43, 15, 2, 2, NULL, 'Branches and Fruitfulness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the fate of branches based on their fruitfulness. The first verse describes branches that do not abide in Christ being cast away, while the second verse discusses branches that do not bear fruit being taken away.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 58, 10, 27, 27, 'cast forth as a branch', 'Judgment and Fiery Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and destruction for those who do not remain faithful. Both passages emphasize the consequences of being cast away and facing fiery indignation.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 61, 2, 20, 20, 'cast forth as a branch', 'Consequences of Abandoning Faith', 'This connection highlights the consequences of failing to remain in Christ. Both passages emphasize the dire outcomes for those who turn away from their faith, leading to destruction.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 6, 26, 19, 12, 14, 'is withered; and men gather them', 'Judgment and Withering Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of being cut off from life and vitality. In John 15:6, branches that do not abide in Christ are withered and burned, paralleling Ezekiel 19:12-14, where branches are broken and consumed by fire, symbolizing judgment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 19, 37, 4, 4, 'abide in me', 'Connection of Desires and Abiding', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between delighting in God and receiving desires. John 15:7''s ''abide in me'' reflects a deep connection that aligns with Psalms 37:4''s promise of fulfilling heart''s desires.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 43, 14, 13, 13, 'ask what ye will', 'Connection of Prayer and Abiding', 'Both passages emphasize the act of asking in relation to a relationship with Jesus. John 15:7 highlights the importance of abiding in Him, while John 14:13 focuses on asking in His name, suggesting a deep connection between these concepts.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 62, 3, 22, 22, 'abide in me', 'Connection of Prayer and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between abiding in Christ and receiving answers to prayers. John 15:7 highlights the importance of having Christ''s words within, while 1 John 3:22 connects receiving from Him to keeping His commandments.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 62, 5, 14, 14, 'ask what ye will', 'Connection of Prayer and Abiding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of asking in alignment with God''s will. John 15:7 highlights the condition of abiding in Christ, while 1 John 5:14 assures that requests made according to His will are heard.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 43, 15, 16, 16, 'ye shall ask what ye will', 'Connection of Abiding and Asking', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of abiding in Christ and the power of prayer. The promise of receiving what is asked for is linked to being chosen and ordained to bear fruit.', 'theme', 0.923, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 40, 7, 7, 7, 'ask what ye will', 'Connection of Asking and Receiving', 'Both passages emphasize the act of asking and receiving from God. John 15:7 highlights that if one abides in Christ, their requests will be fulfilled, while Matthew 7:7 encourages believers to ask, seek, and knock for divine responses.', 'theme', 0.881, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 7, 48, 5, 16, 16, 'abide in me', 'Abiding and Walking in Spirit', 'This connection highlights the importance of abiding in Christ and walking in the Spirit. Both passages emphasize a transformative relationship that leads to fulfilling God''s will rather than succumbing to fleshly desires.', 'theme', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 40, 5, 16, 16, NULL, 'Glorifying the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of good works in glorifying the Father. John 15:8 highlights bearing much fruit, while Matthew 5:16 focuses on letting light shine through good works.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 43, 8, 31, 31, 'my disciples', 'Discipleship and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the criteria for being Jesus'' disciples. Both passages emphasize the importance of bearing fruit and continuing in His word as evidence of true discipleship.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 50, 1, 11, 11, 'glorified, that ye bear much fruit', 'Connection of Fruit and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bearing fruit as a means of glorifying God. John highlights that bearing much fruit glorifies the Father, while Philippians speaks of being filled with the fruits of righteousness for God''s glory.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 47, 9, 10, 15, 'that ye bear much fruit', 'Glorifying God through Fruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of bearing fruit as a demonstration of faith. In John 15:8, bearing much fruit glorifies the Father, while in 2 Corinthians 9:10-15, the fruits of righteousness lead to thanksgiving and glorification of God.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 43, 15, 5, 5, 'bear much fruit', 'Connection of Fruit Bearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of bearing much fruit as a sign of discipleship. The first passage states that bearing fruit glorifies the Father, while the second explains that abiding in Christ is essential for producing that fruit.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 19, 92, 12, 15, 'bear much fruit', 'Flourishing and Bearing Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of flourishing and bearing fruit as a sign of righteousness and discipleship. John 15:8 connects glorifying God with bearing much fruit, while Psalms 92:12-15 describes the righteous flourishing and bringing forth fruit even in old age.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 8, 60, 4, 11, 11, 'that ye bear much fruit', 'Glorifying God Through Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of glorifying God through one''s actions. John 15:8 highlights bearing fruit as a means of glorification, while 1 Peter 4:11 connects speaking and ministering to glorifying God through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 43, 17, 23, 24, 'as the Father hath loved me', 'Connection of Divine Love', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love, specifically how Jesus loves his followers as the Father loves him. This connection highlights the unity and relational aspect of divine love shared among the Father, Son, and believers.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 62, 2, 28, 28, 'continue ye in my love', 'Connection of Abiding in Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of abiding in love and remaining connected to Christ. John 15:9 speaks of continuing in Jesus'' love, while 1 John 2:28 encourages abiding in Him for confidence at His coming.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 43, 15, 13, 13, 'love', 'Connection of Love and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love, with John 15:9 stating Jesus'' love for his followers and John 15:13 illustrating the ultimate expression of love through sacrifice. This connection highlights how Jesus'' love is demonstrated through the willingness to lay down one''s life for others.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 66, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Love of Christ for Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of love, as both passages emphasize Jesus'' love for believers. John 15:9 states, ''as the Father hath loved me, so have I loved you,'' while Revelation 1:5 affirms that Jesus ''loved us'' and redeemed us.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 49, 3, 18, 18, 'continue ye in my love', 'Love and Comprehension Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of love and its vastness. John emphasizes Jesus'' love as foundational, while Ephesians speaks to comprehending the breadth and depth of that love.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 9, 65, 1, 20, 20, NULL, 'Love and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of love and faith. In John 15:9, Jesus emphasizes His love for believers, while Jude 1:20 encourages building faith through prayer, suggesting that love is foundational to spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 15, 10, 43, 14, 15, 15, 'keep my commandments', 'Connection of Love and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between love and obedience to commandments. John 15:10 reflects the idea that keeping commandments leads to abiding in love, which is echoed in John 14:15 where love is shown through keeping commandments.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
